HOUSE BILL 1084
F3 EMERGENCY BILL 6lr1006
By: Montgomery County Delegation
Introduced and read first time: February 10, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: February 18, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Montgomery County – County Board of Education – School Operation
3 Requirements
4 MC 14–26
5 FOR the purpose of authorizing the Montgomery County Board of Education to require
6 public schools within the county to be open for pupil attendance for a minimum
7 number of actual school days or a minimum number of school hours instead of both
8 under certain circumstances; requiring a school open fewer than a certain number of
9 hours or days to provide certain employees an opportunity to make up lost wages;
10 requiring the county board to report to the State Department of Education and the
11 General Assembly on elementary, middle, and high schools open fewer than a certain
12 number of hours or days; and generally relating to school operation requirements
13 and the Montgomery County Board of Education.
14 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
15 Article – Education
16 Section 7–103(a), (g), and (h)
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
20 Article – Education
21 Section 7–103(b) and (d) through (f)
22 Annotated Code of Maryland
